128
00:10:48,451 --> 00:10:51,821
You should come, walk around,

129
00:10:51,821 --> 00:10:55,821
and tell them they're doing great,
so they grow bigger.

130
00:11:00,321 --> 00:11:03,521
Should we get some sun since we're here

131
00:11:03,521 --> 00:11:06,821
and have fun weeding, too?

132
00:11:08,321 --> 00:11:12,421
Let's. Let's have fun weeding

133
00:11:12,421 --> 00:11:15,721
- and clear our thoughts, too.
- Okay.

134
00:11:52,651 --> 00:11:54,201
Hello.

135
00:12:03,861 --> 00:12:05,731
It's too hot.

136
00:12:05,731 --> 00:12:07,861
Let's call it a day.

137
00:12:13,761 --> 00:12:15,231
Take care.

138
00:12:32,861 --> 00:12:35,241
Why won't the color deepen?

139
00:12:35,241 --> 00:12:37,591
Is it because I switched the soy sauce?

140
00:12:37,591 --> 00:12:39,141
Is it?

141
00:12:41,451 --> 00:12:43,361
Why are you sweating so much?

142
00:12:44,281 --> 00:12:47,071
I'm sweating because we're making broth.

143
00:12:47,071 --> 00:12:48,121
I know.

144
00:12:48,121 --> 00:12:51,621
The vegetables are boiling.
But why are you sweating?

145
00:12:59,421 --> 00:13:02,021
Gosh, you have a fever.

146
00:13:04,221 --> 00:13:08,321
- You're right.
- You got sick from jumping into the ocean.

147
00:13:08,321 --> 00:13:10,221
- I mean-
- I'm okay.

148
00:13:10,221 --> 00:13:13,321
I'm really okay.

149
00:13:17,591 --> 00:13:19,121
You aren't okay.

150
00:13:19,121 --> 00:13:20,781
You need to rest.

151
00:13:21,711 --> 00:13:23,261
Follow me.

152
00:13:23,261 --> 00:13:27,301
We have a guest room for times like this.

153
00:13:28,721 --> 00:13:32,501
Look at your sweat. Goodness. My gosh.

154
00:13:33,721 --> 00:13:37,121
I'm okay.

155
00:13:37,121 --> 00:13:42,111
I recover quickly after taking a quick nap.

156
00:13:42,111 --> 00:13:43,561
Gosh.

157
00:13:44,881 --> 00:13:47,121
I want you to promise me.

158
00:13:47,121 --> 00:13:50,021
Not when you think you're okay,

159
00:13:50,021 --> 00:13:53,971
but come back to work
when you've completely recovered.

160
00:13:53,971 --> 00:13:57,121
I'm really strong.

161
00:13:57,121 --> 00:14:00,571
I said I can work with full energy tomorrow.

162
00:14:01,421 --> 00:14:05,121
Unexpectedly, you follow your head.

163
00:14:05,121 --> 00:14:06,791
I've been told...

164
00:14:06,791 --> 00:14:09,981
I have the brain of a genius

165
00:14:09,981 --> 00:14:11,821
pretty often.

166
00:14:11,821 --> 00:14:14,321
Not your brain. Your head.

167
00:14:14,321 --> 00:14:18,821
You look like you'd follow your heart,
but you follow your head.

168
00:14:18,821 --> 00:14:21,711
Your body is saying, "I'm sick."

169
00:14:21,711 --> 00:14:23,931
But your head is saying, "No, you're strong."

170
00:14:23,931 --> 00:14:26,401
Why won't you listen to your body?

171
00:14:27,271 --> 00:14:29,151
When you're having a hard time,

172
00:14:29,151 --> 00:14:31,841
you need to know how to bend and fall.

173
00:14:31,841 --> 00:14:34,231
That makes you truly strong.

174
00:14:37,021 --> 00:14:42,891
Rest well and come back
with a healthy body and mind.

175
00:14:42,891 --> 00:14:44,541
Sleep.

176
00:15:02,561 --> 00:15:04,981
Why won't you ask me anything?

177
00:15:06,581 --> 00:15:09,501
A few words can't comfort you.

178
00:15:11,021 --> 00:15:12,991
I'll just...

179
00:15:12,991 --> 00:15:15,241
be by your side quietly.

180
00:15:20,551 --> 00:15:24,201
And if you no longer want to wander alone

181
00:15:24,201 --> 00:15:27,841
or you've sorted things out... Anyway,

182
00:15:27,841 --> 00:15:30,641
if you need someone at some point,

183
00:15:32,021 --> 00:15:34,591
I'll be by your side then, too.

184
00:16:57,161 --> 00:16:59,101
How's it? Is it good?

185
00:17:00,521 --> 00:17:02,121
Hey.

186
00:17:02,121 --> 00:17:04,251
- Are you ready to go?
- Yeah.

187
00:17:04,251 --> 00:17:07,521
Aren't you too underdressed for a conference?

188
00:17:07,521 --> 00:17:11,621
I'm not presenting. Aren't I
just supposed to clap hard?

189
00:17:13,041 --> 00:17:14,551
Is that right?

190
00:17:16,161 --> 00:17:17,611
They're here.

191
00:17:26,521 --> 00:17:29,421
I didn't know she was so pretty.

192
00:17:29,421 --> 00:17:33,221
Her scarf is nice, too. She's like Audrey Hepburn.

193
00:17:33,221 --> 00:17:35,701
- Isn't the scarf too much?
- It's too much.

194
00:17:35,701 --> 00:17:37,601
It'd make her neck sweaty.

195
00:17:37,601 --> 00:17:39,821
She'll step on it or get it caught in a door.

196
00:17:39,821 --> 00:17:43,621
That'd be better. If you get caught
on a car window, you die.

197
00:17:45,981 --> 00:17:48,481
Why is her skin so taut?

198
00:17:48,481 --> 00:17:50,211
Look at Ji An.

199
00:17:50,211 --> 00:17:53,141
She hit the passage of time honestly with her face.

200
00:17:53,141 --> 00:17:54,321
That's enough.

201
00:17:54,321 --> 00:17:57,431
Should I bring out my jewelry?

202
00:17:57,431 --> 00:17:59,221
You're falling behind in looks.

203
00:17:59,221 --> 00:18:02,161
